  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Global Product -Disability</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Irish Aid funding will support the ILO Global Product on Disability Inclusion which will form be part of the management response to recommendations in the final independent evaluation of disability-related projects in Phase 3 of the ILO/IA PP. The Global Product will support country level activities to be proposed under Phase 4 of the ILO/IA PP, through the development of practical tools for advocacy, policy advice and capacity building; through collaboration with ILO and other UN partners on approaches to the gathering of comprehensive statistics on the labour market situation of persons with disabilities; the establishment and strengthening of a recognised network of Disability Equality Training (DET) facilitators; the development of impact indicators; and the delivery of training programmes in collaboration with the International Training Centre, Turin.</narrative>
  </description>
